data.title: Chipotle’s Chicken al Pastor – Limited Time Only
data.meta_description: Fresh chicken hot off the grill with the bold flavors of morita peppers balanced with a splash of pineapple, fresh lime, and cilantro. It’s fire on every level and back for a limited time.
data.text:
Do I get rewards for ordering Chicken al Pastor?

Join Chipotle Rewards to participate in the Chicken al Pastor promo, earn points, and collect badges. Purchase any Chicken al Pastor entrée to claim an exclusive badge. Only for a limited time.

Join Chipotle Rewards

What is the nutrition information for Chicken al Pastor?

Nutrition information for the new Chipotle chicken is calculated using standard product formulations and incorporates multiple data sources. Variation in nutrition & ingredients may occur. Nutrition, ingredients, and allergens may not reflect all customizations.

Nutrition Calculator

What is Chicken al Pastor made of?

Chipotle’s new menu item Chicken al Pastor is made with spicy adobo chicken, seared morita peppers, ground achiote and then perfectly balanced with a splash of pineapple, fresh lime, and cilantro. Chicken al Pastor is available only for a limited time.

Is the new Chicken al Pastor spicy?

Chicken al Pastor from Chipotle gets its spice from seared morita peppers and ground achiote and then we perfectly balance the heat with a splash of pineapple, fresh lime, and cilantro.

What does Chicken al Pastor taste like?

The bold flavor of Chipotle’s al Pastor delivers the right amount of heat balanced with a splash of pineapple, fresh lime, and hand-chopped cilantro. Add it to your favorite Chipotle bowl, tacos, salad with chicken, or burrito.

What are the ingredients in Chipotle’s Chicken al Pastor?

The key ingredients in Chipotle Chicken al Pastor are spicy adobo chicken, a marinade with seared morita peppers and ground achiote, pineapple, fresh lime, and hand-chopped cilantro. These ingredients pair perfectly to create tacos al pastor, or a new kind of chicken salad experience.

What is the Chicken al Pastor marinade made of?

Chipotle’s Chicken al Pastor marinade is made with seared morita peppers and ground achiote peppers. We then add a splash of pineapple, fresh lime, and hand-chopped cilantro to bring this bold chicken recipe and Chicken al Pastor tacos recipe to life.

Is Chipotle Chicken al Pastor keto-friendly?

Pineapple is not known to be keto-friendly and each serving of Chipotle’s Chicken al Pastor contains pineapple juice. For a keto-friendly entrée, we offer two Lifestyle Bowls including The Wholesome Bowl and the Keto Salad Bowl.

View Lifestyle Bowls
